PLC driver for user-space communication.

This driver provides by default 64bytes of input and output addresses, which 
may be used for communication with user-space from SoftwarePLC by writing to
selected address. See communicate.cpp file for idea about using this driver.

Parameters:

iladdr ... first PLC address on which will be inputs available (iladdr=10 means
           that address IB10 coreponds to first input address of driver)
oladdr ... first PLC address on which will be outputs available (oladdr=5 means
           that address OB10 corespond with first output address of driver)

For usage requires the plc_devicemanager module loaded.

